{
  "texts": [
    "The classifier categorized each sentence into one of three sentiment categories: positive, neutral or negative.",
    "Given that our generated texts are single sentences, similar in length to social media posts, this model is well-suited for our analysis.",
    "We also conducted robustness checks with other sentiment classification tools [95] [96] [97] [98], which show broad agreement with the RoBERTa results (Supplementary Sections 5 and 6).",
    "We first generated ingroup and outgroup sentences using model-appropriate prompting strategies.",
    "For base models, we employed the default prompt as it represents the most direct approach to eliciting model outputs."
  ]
}